children.subject: +1 Curious to know this as well.

history.content: I was able to find a group through Piazza (in the beginning of the semester, they set up a Piazza group-forming page), and luckily my team was pretty good; however, I would still suggest asking around and trying to meet people who are also going to take 162 (maybe CS/Engineering club meetings, info sessions, finding mutual friends, etc.) because you never how good your team will be if you randomly select one through Piazza.

I'm considering taking CS 162 next semester. However, I don't know anyone else taking the course. (I am a freshman. All my friends are taking 61C in Fall 17.) Has anyone else gone into 162 without a team of 4? How did you find your partners (considering most people will already have them coming in)? Did you end up with a good team?
history.subject: Finding partners for CS 162
